g.text: SNS is a fully managed messaging service that allows you to send messages from subscribers to multiple subscribers via "publish-subscribe" model
Publish-Subscribe Pattern: Publishers sends message to topics and those messages are sent to subscribers of the topics.
Topics: Topic is an access point for subscribers to receive notifications.
Publishers: Applications or users that publish messages to an SNS topic.
Subscribers: Application or users that subscribe to receive messages from an SNS topic.
* "event producer" only sends message to one SNS topic
* As many "event receivers" as we want to listen to SNS topic notification.
* Each subscriber to the topic will get all the messages.
* Client-side encryption if client wants to perform encryption and decryption itself.
* Access Controls: IAM policies to regulate access to SNS API.
* SNS Access Policies: Similar to S3 bucket policy. Cross account access, allowing other services to write to SNS
